cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.HC, cs.MM 

The paper deals with automated bone age assessment using radiographs, which involves image processing and machine learning techniques. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the use of classifiers and regression models for predicting bone age, which falls under the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also mentions the importance of ethnicity and sex on age development, which could be related to information retrieval (cs.IR) or human-computer interaction (cs.HC). Finally, the paper deals with medical imaging, which could be related to multimedia (cs.MM).
